               <p>GEORGE BRIGGS. I am a <rs id="t18281023-207-viclabel1209" type="occupation">boot and shoemaker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18281023-207-victim1077 t18281023-207-viclabel1209"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18281023-207-crimeloc1210">Mile-end-road</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18281023-207-crimeloc1210" type="placeName" value="Mile-end-road"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18281023-207-crimeloc1210" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18281023-207-off1207 t18281023-207-crimeloc1210"></join>. On the 21st of October, I was in my back-room, and saw the prisoner take two pairs of shoes from my shop, about eleven o'clock in the morning - he took down six pairs; four pairs fell down, and he took two pairs off - I pursued him: he threw them down- I took them up, and pursued; he was taken by the officer, in my sight - they had been hanging by the side of my door-post.</p>
